narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: DS Philosophy is just amazing. Take it!
yes, it's a great introduction to philosophy

Stick with March. He's awesome. This is a great class. You will not be lectured at. This is an intense Socratic dialogue with the professor. You will probably leave more confused than anything else, but it's a great experience. Be proactive and talk to him.

I would highly recommend DS Philosophy to another student; although the material is challenging, the lectures and discussions were so intellectually stimulating that I found myself pondering over their topics out of class on several occasions. This course made me appreciate and become interested in philosophy, and is a great introduction to Western Philosophy.
A solid introduction, invaluable for anyone interested in ancient or modern philosophy. Rather enjoyable.
